      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:4:7:3",
      "text": [
        " مَا أَخَذَتِ الْحِبَالَةُ فَقَطَعَتْ مِنْهُ شَيْئاً فَهُوَ مَيِّتٌ وَ مَا أَدْرَكْتَ مِنْ سَائِرِ جَسَدِهِ حَيّاً فَذَكِّهِ ثُمَّ كُلْ مِنْهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Al Husayn Bin Muhammad, from Moala Bin Muhammad, from Al Washa, from Abdul Rahman Bin Abu Abdullah, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘What the snare seizes, so something is cut off from it, so it is dead, and what you come to from the rest of its body, so purify (slaughter) it, then eat from it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Al-Husayn from Muhammad has narrated from Mu‘alla’ ibn Muhammad from al-Washsha’ from ‘Abd al-Rahman ibn abu ‘Abd Allah who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Whatever of a prey is caught in the snare is dead and whatever of the rest of the body you find alive, slaughter it properly; then you can use it for food.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
    "verse_translations": [
      "en.hubeali",
      "en.sarwar"
